  "title": "System Application Engineer| FPGA / DSP / MCU Electrical Design",
  "description": "<ul><li><p><strong>Role: System Application Engineer [ Electrical ]</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Manufacturer of Scanning System for Car Park, Checkpoints & Airport</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>5 Days Per Week</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>SG Office: Jurong East, Singapore - Tradehub 21</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Basic Salary: $2,800 - $4,500 + 14 Days AL</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Entitled to Yearly $500 Medical Benefits + Yearly Performance Bonus</strong></p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p><p>1. Bachelor’s degree or higher in Electrical Engineering or a related field.</p><p>2. Min 1-3 years of working experience in electrical field.</p><p>3. This role is required to <em><strong>visit site [ SG ] if required</strong></em></p><p><em><strong>4. Opportunity to travel globally </strong></em>[ Thailand, UAE ... ] for system evaluations, custom installations, and training purposes.<br /><br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p></p><ul><li><p><strong>Design and improve X-ray scan systems for car park surveillance system or scanning system in Airport or Checkpoint, including building prototypes and testing new designs.</strong></p></li><li><p>Write manufacturing and test procedures for equipment.</p></li><li><p>Install, repair, and maintain equipment in the field while providing customer training as needed.</p></li><li><p>Train manufacturing personnel on assembly and testing of products.</p></li><li><p>Assist in integrating software with electrical control systems.</p></li><li><p>Provide organized documentation for analysis and recommend design improvements.</p></li><li><p>Assemble, test, and troubleshoot product designs, offering constructive feedback.</p></li><li><p>Evaluate product performance using field data and recommend modifications or improvements.</p></li><li><p>Perform other duties as required.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Must familiar to one of the skills set below,</strong></p><ol><li><p>FPGA / DSP / MCU design expertise.</p></li><li><p>Experience with interface applications such as Ethernet or PCI.</p></li><li><p>Proficiency in programming languages like C++/C# or HDL language.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with electronic testing equipment (e.g., oscilloscopes, digital multi-meters).<br /></p><p></p></li></ol><p>#SCR-carson-cheong</p><p>⭕ Cheong Kar Chun ⭕ Team Manager ⭕ R1980386</p><p>⭕ The Supreme HR Advisory ⭕ 14C7279</p>",
